Subject: [PATCH 1483/2066] arm64: dts: r8a7795-salvator-x: Add i2c-rcar
 support

This patch enables I2C ch4 for Salvator-X board on R8A7795 SoC.

The default I2C bus clock rate of I2C ch4 sets 400 kHz. Each following
I2C device connected to I2C ch4 of Salvator-X board on R8A7796 SoC is
supporting the bus clock of 400 kHz:

    PCA9654, 9FGV0841, ADV7482WBBCZ, MAX9611, 5P49V5923

Signed-off-by: Hiromitsu Yamasaki <hiromitsu.yamasaki.ym@renesas.com>
Signed-off-by: Takeshi Kihara <takeshi.kihara.df@renesas.com>
[zou:Original patch taken from
git://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/horms/renesas-bsp.git
 v4.9/rcar-3.5.1]
Signed-off-by: zou cao <cao.zou@windriver.com>
---
 arch/arm64/boot/dts/renesas/r8a7795-salvator-x.dts |    6 ++++++
 1 files changed, 6 insertions(+), 0 deletions(-)

diff --git a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/renesas/r8a7795-salvator-x.dts b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/renesas/r8a7795-salvator-x.dts
index c66e1d5..e5f26c2 100644
--- a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/renesas/r8a7795-salvator-x.dts
+++ b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/renesas/r8a7795-salvator-x.dts
@@ -531,6 +531,12 @@
 	};
 };
 
+&i2c4 {
+	status = "okay";
+
+	clock-frequency = <400000>;
+};
+
 &rcar_sound {
 	pinctrl-0 = <&sound_pins &sound_clk_pins>;
 	pinctrl-names = "default";
